                <note rend="inline" type="source">026 China/8–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-26T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 26, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 26—4:21 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1426. To date Chinese public has been given only violent attacks on White Paper
                    with quotations torn from context. Even “reference material” circulated within
                    party and in certain university circles reputedly inadequate. Desire noted some
                    Chinese circles for complete text White Paper to read US Government story
                    without omissions of Communist editing. Request Department mail Peiping via Hong
                    Kong six copies separately wrapped.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
